I am not usually a fan of breakfast food but Cliff's Cafe & Catering changed my mind. I ordered a mushroom, ham & cheese omelet with white toast an order of home fries. & coffee. To say that their food was good would be doing Cliff's Cafe an injustice. The coffee was fresh and got, the omelet was HUGE, fresh and simply amazing. Normally when I get home fries at any breakfast place the potatoes are very bland but not at Cliff's. The cook seasons the potatoes perfectly.  I have never finished a plate filled with breakfast food until now. I left there a very satisfied customer. I will most definitely be visiting again.

So as you can tell, I rate it a total success.

Lets start with this. Wife ordered egg beaters because she's allergic to the yellow part of the egg. Not because she's a hipster and we like to pay 50 cents more for eggs. Well, she's now very sick, and the plans we had for later are now gone out the window.  Thanks for that. From the moment we got there, my family didn't feel welcome. Asked for a highchair for the baby, never got one until some random person brought our food and had to ask again. 3 people were sat at least 5 mins after my family, and they had drinks long before someone even acknowledged our presence.
